config BR2_PACKAGE_IOEXAMPLE8
    bool "Example8: Serial RS-485 Interactive Demo"
    help
      This package provides a simple interactive demo that configures and
      communicates over a serial RS-485 interface (e.g., /dev/ttySTM1) on
      an STM32F4-based board.

      Features:
        - Opens and configures a serial port at 115200 baud (8N1)
        - Enables RS-485 mode via ioctl (TIOCSRS485)
        - Sends user-typed messages from the terminal
        - Waits for transmission completion (tcdrain)
        - Gracefully exits on empty input
        - (Optional) Receives responses with a 100ms timeout

      Usage:
        $ ioexample8 [<tty device>]
        Defaults to /dev/ttySTM1 if not specified.

      Dependencies:
        - Standard Linux serial interface
        - <linux/serial.h>, termios, ioctl
        - https://github.com/vsergeev/c-periphery (reference)

      Example:
        $ ioexample8 /dev/ttySTM1

      Note:
        The program uses VMIN/VTIME settings for blocking read with timeout.
        RS-485 flags are configured as:
          - SER_RS485_ENABLED
          - SER_RS485_RTS_ON_SEND
          - ~SER_RS485_RTS_AFTER_SEND

      This demo is useful for verifying UART/RS-485 wiring and behavior.